The Oblitercons/Imprisoner/Predator/Choran/Nemesis Enforcer/Scattershot:




Dark One soared overhead the other nine Alliance members he was with, in a 
foul mood.  He should be commanding the mission, but some psychotic robot was 
in charge.

---

Breakdown rested comfortably in a chair inside Pyro's tank mode.  "Speed it 
up you big hunk of scrap.  I want to actually get to the battle in the next 
twenty-four hours."

"Shut up!" a disembodied voice retorted, the voice filling the entire tank.  
"If you don't like my speed, get the slag out."

---

Hiss sat inside a chair as well, this one being the drivers seat to 
Scavenger's HUMV mode.  The scientist-like warrior looked around, examining 
the terrain as they neared the middle of the dark continent.  "There's to 
much green."

"I agree." Scavenger replied, the conversation ending there.

---

Imprisoner drove in his armored carrier vehicle mode, both of his companions 
inside.

"We should lay low now that Unitron and his group are dead.  No point in 
seeking them out.  We should signal our craft and get off this worthless 
planetoid." 

"I'm with Imprisoner."

"Yeah." Choran sighed.  "I guess.  But AFTER, we kick Maximal tailpipe!"

---

Nemesis Enforcer's great leathery wings beat against the air, and the 
boosters in his feet shot out near invisible jets of flames, sending him 
rocketing faster than anyone, Scattershot a couple yards behind and a few 
more below.
